10:01.518 --> 10:02.269
Right.

10:02.310 --> 10:03.311
No, wait!

10:03.353 --> 10:04.645
It's Francis.

10:04.687 --> 10:07.107
We can't just take

10:04.687 --> 10:07.107
Mom's word for it.

10:07.148 --> 10:09.276
Hey, Malcolm, everything okay?

10:09.317 --> 10:10.902
Um, Francis...

10:10.944 --> 10:13.029
we were just

10:10.944 --> 10:13.029
wondering...

10:13.071 --> 10:14.822
Mom said...

10:14.864 --> 10:17.658
you ratted on us

10:14.864 --> 10:17.658
about Dewey's bike.

10:17.700 --> 10:20.661
But she's probably

10:17.700 --> 10:20.661
just mixed up, right?

10:20.703 --> 10:23.248
Because you're our big brother

10:20.703 --> 10:23.248
and you wouldn't do

10:23.290 --> 10:24.707
something like

10:23.290 --> 10:24.707
that-- Francis?

10:24.749 --> 10:26.084
You don't know

10:26.126 --> 10:27.835
what kind of pressure

10:26.126 --> 10:27.835
I was under!

10:27.877 --> 10:28.836
You butt-wipe!

10:28.878 --> 10:30.046
How could you?

10:30.088 --> 10:31.339
Well, did he do it?

10:31.381 --> 10:32.673
I can't believe you!

10:32.715 --> 10:33.674
You're our big brother!

10:33.716 --> 10:35.843
You're supposed

10:33.716 --> 10:35.843
to protect us,

10:33.716 --> 10:35.843
not betray us.

10:35.885 --> 10:37.471
He did it, didn't he?

10:37.512 --> 10:39.473
Malcolm, just let me explain...

10:37.512 --> 10:39.473
And then you actually

10:39.514 --> 10:42.267
have the nerve to ask us

10:39.514 --> 10:42.267
to risk our butts for you?

10:42.309 --> 10:44.685
Maybe we should just

10:42.309 --> 10:44.685
give the letter to Mom.

10:44.727 --> 10:46.938
No, you can't do that!

10:44.727 --> 10:46.938
Yeah, why not?

10:46.980 --> 10:49.107
Because if you give

10:46.980 --> 10:49.107
the letter to Mom,

10:49.149 --> 10:50.691
she'll know it's not Sunday.

10:50.733 --> 10:53.694
I'll just tell her it

10:50.733 --> 10:53.694
came special delivery.

