But then she'll know

10:59.742 --> 11:01.702
you can forge her signature.

11:01.744 --> 11:02.870
Which won't

11:01.744 --> 11:02.870
matter at all

11:02.912 --> 11:04.539
because she'll be

11:02.912 --> 11:04.539
so mad at you,

11:04.581 --> 11:06.707
she won't even think

11:04.581 --> 11:06.707
about me for a few days.

11:06.749 --> 11:08.502
And even if she does,

11:06.749 --> 11:08.502
I'll just tell her

11:08.543 --> 11:09.710
I didn't want

11:08.543 --> 11:09.710
to disturb her.

11:09.752 --> 11:11.129
So in addition to

11:09.752 --> 11:11.129
you getting nailed,

11:11.171 --> 11:12.713
I'll get points for

11:11.171 --> 11:12.713
being sympathetic.

11:12.755 --> 11:16.092
Put Reese on the phone.

11:16.134 --> 11:18.303
You know, Hal,

11:16.134 --> 11:18.303
owning a Porsche

11:18.345 --> 11:20.721
is not just for

11:18.345 --> 11:20.721
the wealthy anymore.

11:20.763 --> 11:22.723
My lifemate and I,

11:20.763 --> 11:22.723
we both drive 'em.

11:22.765 --> 11:23.891
Really?

11:23.933 --> 11:25.684
Oh, she's a very

11:23.933 --> 11:25.684
lucky lady.

11:27.937 --> 11:30.148
Oh. A blond.

11:32.775 --> 11:33.985
This is going to

11:32.775 --> 11:33.985
sound clichéd, Hal,

11:34.027 --> 11:35.903
but what can I do to put you

11:34.027 --> 11:35.903
in that car today?

11:35.945 --> 11:37.905
You can give me $90,000.

11:37.947 --> 11:39.782
(both laughing)

11:39.824 --> 11:41.201
That's funny.

11:41.242 --> 11:42.785
Yeah.

11:41.242 --> 11:42.785
Seriously, we have

11:42.827 --> 11:45.746
all kinds of financial plans

11:42.827 --> 11:45.746
available.

11:45.788 --> 11:46.747
(sighs)

11:46.789 --> 11:48.333
Why don't we take it

11:46.789 --> 11:48.333
for a test drive?

11:48.375 --> 11:50.335
Nah, I... I don't know.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.587
I would have to call work and...

11:52.629 --> 11:54.381
There's a phone...

11:54.422 --> 11:56.424
in the car.

11:59.177 --> 12:00.595
So, do we give Mom

11:59.177 --> 12:00.595
the letter now

12:00.637 --> 12:02.805
or wait till Dad gets home

12:00.637 --> 12:02.805
and give him both barrels?

12:02.847 --> 12:04.015
Now!

12:04.057 --> 12:05.766
Do it now!

12:05.808 --> 12:06.934
We're not giving

12:05.808 --> 12:06.934
Mom the letter.

12:06.976 --> 12:07.977
Of course we are!

12:08.019 --> 12:09.020
We have to!

12:09.062 --> 12:09.979
He's a traitor!

12:10.021 --> 12:11.231
He has to pay!

12:11.272 --> 12:12.607
He must suffer!

12:12.649 --> 12:14.651
We can't give

12:12.649 --> 12:14.651
Mom the letter.

12:12.649 --> 12:14.651
She'd kill him.

12:14.693 --> 12:17.362
But we can make him

12:14.693 --> 12:17.362
think we're giving

12:14.693 --> 12:17.362
her the letter.

12:17.404 --> 12:18.446
We could make

12:17.404 --> 12:18.446
him think

12:18.488 --> 12:20.031
we're scuzzy,

12:18.488 --> 12:20.031
dirty backstabbers

12:20.073 --> 12:21.575
just like he is.

12:21.616 --> 12:22.783
Oh, okay.

12:22.825 --> 12:25.786
(phone rings)

12:25.828 --> 12:27.788
Hello.

12:25.828 --> 12:27.788
Hey, it's me.

12:27.830 --> 12:29.165
Well, if it isn't

12:27.830 --> 12:29.165
the snitch.

12:29.207 --> 12:30.791
Hi, snitch.

12:30.833 --> 12:32.377
Come on, Malcolm.

12:32.419 --> 12:34.837
Let's just end this

12:32.419 --> 12:34.837
before it gets out

12:32.419 --> 12:34.837
of control.

12:34.879 --> 12:36.381
I know how you

12:34.879 --> 12:36.381
guys feel.

12:36.423 --> 12:38.174
You do, huh?

12:36.423 --> 12:38.174
How do we feel?

12:38.216 --> 12:40.801
Well... bad.

12:40.843 --> 12:41.802
No.

12:41.844 --> 12:42.970
The words that

12:41.844 --> 12:42.970
come to my mind

12:43.012 --> 12:46.974
are revenge,

12:43.012 --> 12:46.974
payback, envelope.

12:47.016 --> 12:49.018
Malcolm, you're not going

12:47.016 --> 12:49.018
to give Mom the letter.

12:49.060 --> 12:51.479
I don't think you're in

12:49.060 --> 12:51.479
any position to call the shots.

12:51.521 --> 12:53.814
No, but... Richie should be

12:51.521 --> 12:53.814
right about now.

12:53.856 --> 12:55.442
Richie?

12:53.856 --> 12:55.442
Yeah?

12:57.860 --> 13:01.406
That was the best 12 minutes

12:57.860 --> 13:01.406
of my life.

13:01.448 --> 13:03.199
Well, I'm glad

13:01.448 --> 13:03.199
to hear that, Hal.

13:03.241 --> 13:05.410
You know, there are

13:03.241 --> 13:05.410
a couple of people

13:05.452 --> 13:06.703
I'd like you to meet.

13:11.874 --> 13:13.627
FRANCIS:

13:11.874 --> 13:13.627
Okay, listen up:

13:13.668 --> 13:16.837
my mom's in her bedroom,

13:13.668 --> 13:16.837
so you gotta keep it down,

13:16.879 --> 13:19.090
and remember,

13:16.879 --> 13:19.090
don't hurt my brothers.

13:19.132 --> 13:20.216
(glass breaking)

13:20.258 --> 13:21.842
Circus!

13:21.884 --> 13:23.261
It's okay. It was ugly.

13:23.303 --> 13:24.638
Man, just get the letter

13:24.679 --> 13:26.847
and don't let Malcolm

13:24.679 --> 13:26.847
out of your sight.

13:26.889 --> 13:28.433
He's too smart.

13:28.475 --> 13:29.517
Uh-oh.

13:29.559 --> 13:31.102
What do you mean, "uh-oh"?

13:29.559 --> 13:31.102
What did he do?

13:31.144 --> 13:32.270
He's out of breath.

13:32.312 --> 13:34.439
Damn it!

13:32.312 --> 13:34.439
He hid the letter.

13:34.481 --> 13:35.690
Okay, kid,

13:34.481 --> 13:35.690
you've got

13:35.732 --> 13:36.857
three seconds to tell me

13:36.899 --> 13:38.526
or I'm going to pound you

13:36.899 --> 13:38.526
within an...

13:38.568 --> 13:39.860
Richie!

13:39.902 --> 13:41.279
Which part

13:39.902 --> 13:41.279
of "no hurting my brothers"

13:41.321 --> 13:42.322
didn't you understand?

13:42.363 --> 13:43.657
I got to tell you, man,

13:43.698 --> 13:44.865
you're not allowing me

13:44.907 --> 13:46.743
a single creative

13:44.907 --> 13:46.743
thought here.

13:46.785 --> 13:48.911
(whispering):

13:46.785 --> 13:48.911
Where'd you put it?

13:48.953 --> 13:50.330
In the VCR.

13:48.953 --> 13:50.330
I know.

13:50.371 --> 13:51.872
If we set fire

13:50.371 --> 13:51.872
to the house,

13:51.914 --> 13:53.874
Malcolm will go

13:51.914 --> 13:53.874
right for the letter.

13:53.916 --> 13:55.543
Why would he go

13:53.916 --> 13:55.543
right for the letter?

13:55.585 --> 13:58.463
Well, maybe we should

13:55.585 --> 13:58.463
just set fire to the

13:55.585 --> 13:58.463
house and find out.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.047
Put Justin on the phone.

14:00.089 --> 14:01.882
You the man, Francis.

14:01.924 --> 14:02.883
You the man!

14:02.925 --> 14:04.552
Put Richie back on the phone.

14:04.594 --> 14:06.346
Hey, you can tear up

14:04.594 --> 14:06.346
the house if you want

14:06.387 --> 14:08.348
with my mom here

14:06.387 --> 14:08.348
and explain it to her

14:08.389 --> 14:10.057
or you can quit

14:08.389 --> 14:10.057
and slink away

14:10.099 --> 14:12.893
like the monosyllabic

14:10.099 --> 14:12.893
mouth-breathers you are.

14:12.935 --> 14:13.936
What'd he say?

14:13.978 --> 14:15.480
He said a lot of things,

14:15.522 --> 14:18.566
but the gist of it is,

14:15.522 --> 14:18.566
we got to tear up the house.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.694
No, you can't do that. Just...

14:20.735 --> 14:22.278
wait a minute,

14:20.735 --> 14:22.278
I have an idea.

14:22.320 --> 14:23.530
Look at Reese.

14:23.571 --> 14:24.781
What's he doing?

14:24.823 --> 14:26.324
He's just

14:24.823 --> 14:26.324
sitting there.

14:26.366 --> 14:28.284
No, look at his eyes.

14:26.366 --> 14:28.284
What are his eyes doing?

14:28.326 --> 14:29.703
They're looking back at me.

14:29.744 --> 14:31.329
Okay, just keep looking at him.

14:49.972 --> 14:52.099
He's looking at the VCR.

14:52.141 --> 14:54.728
No, I-I was looking at the...

14:52.141 --> 14:54.728
the other thing.

14:54.769 --> 14:56.437
Bingo! We got it!

14:58.398 --> 15:01.108
JUSTIN:

14:58.398 --> 15:01.108
You're the man, Richie!

15:01.150 --> 15:02.360
All right!

15:02.402 --> 15:04.445
Who wants a latte?

15:08.783 --> 15:10.326
I'm really sorry,

15:08.783 --> 15:10.326
you guys.

15:10.368 --> 15:11.952
For what?

15:11.994 --> 15:13.204
You were perfect.

15:13.246 --> 15:15.540
You did exactly

15:13.246 --> 15:15.540
what I thought you'd do.

15:15.582 --> 15:17.417
What are you

15:15.582 --> 15:17.417
talking about?

15:17.458 --> 15:18.585
They have a fake letter.

15:18.626 --> 15:19.960
I knew Francis

15:18.626 --> 15:19.960
wouldn't leave us alone

15:20.002 --> 15:20.961
without getting something

15:21.003 --> 15:22.797
and I knew you'd give it away.

15:22.839 --> 15:25.216
I knew exactly

15:22.839 --> 15:25.216
what everyone would do.

15:25.258 --> 15:26.967
So where's the

15:25.258 --> 15:26.967
real letter?

15:27.009 --> 15:28.845
I had to think

15:27.009 --> 15:28.845
of the one place

15:28.887 --> 15:30.388
they'd never think

15:28.887 --> 15:30.388
of looking.

15:30.430 --> 15:31.972
I had to give it

15:30.430 --> 15:31.972
to the one person

15:32.014 --> 15:32.973
they'd never think

15:33.015 --> 15:33.974
I'd give it to.

15:34.016 --> 15:35.351
I did the most

15:34.016 --> 15:35.351
brilliant thing of all:

15:35.393 --> 15:36.561
I gave it to Dewey.

15:36.603 --> 15:38.979
And I hid it

15:36.603 --> 15:38.979
under Mom's pillow.

15:39.021 --> 15:40.398
You what?!

15:49.407 --> 15:51.992
I'm gonna kill him.

15:52.034 --> 15:54.036
I am going

15:52.034 --> 15:54.036
to kill him!

15:54.078 --> 15:57.039
(making ghostly sounds)

15:57.081 --> 15:59.166
This is all a dream.

15:59.208 --> 16:00.251
Oh, shut up, Reese!

16:00.293 --> 16:01.210
Mom, stop it.

16:01.252 --> 16:02.253
You're sick.

16:02.295 --> 16:03.588
I'm too mad to be sick.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.590
No, he has finally

16:03.630 --> 16:05.590
done it this time.

16:05.632 --> 16:06.883
Where is that brochure

16:06.925 --> 16:08.676
for the work farm

16:06.925 --> 16:08.676
in Arizona?

16:08.718 --> 16:11.596
He thinks military school

16:08.718 --> 16:11.596
is tough?

16:11.638 --> 16:13.890
Just wait.

16:13.932 --> 16:15.850
Wait.

16:17.226 --> 16:18.269
Wait...

16:18.311 --> 16:19.395
wait...

16:19.437 --> 16:20.897
wait!

16:22.440 --> 16:25.025
(Lois retching)

16:25.067 --> 16:26.026
Hey, Malcolm?

16:26.068 --> 16:27.027
Hi, Francis.

16:27.069 --> 16:28.446
Look, I'm sorry about all this.

16:28.488 --> 16:29.489
I shouldn't have

16:29.530 --> 16:30.865
sent those guys over.

16:30.907 --> 16:31.866
It was stupid.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.033
You know, Francis,

16:33.075 --> 16:35.411
we never actually intended

16:33.075 --> 16:35.411
to show the letter to Mom.

16:35.453 --> 16:37.037
We just wanted to scare you.

16:37.079 --> 16:38.205
Yeah, I know.

16:38.247 --> 16:39.707
You guys would never

16:38.247 --> 16:39.707
do that to me.

16:39.749 --> 16:41.041
But if she did see the letter,

16:41.083 --> 16:43.711
you'd know it was just

16:41.083 --> 16:43.711
an accident, right?

16:43.753 --> 16:45.254
Yeah, but Richie has the letter.

16:47.298 --> 16:49.425
Please tell me

16:47.298 --> 16:49.425
Richie has the letter.

16:49.467 --> 16:51.302
Richie has coupons.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.012
Mom has the letter.

16:54.472 --> 16:57.057
But like I said, it was just

16:54.472 --> 16:57.057
an accident. I swear.

16:57.099 --> 17:00.060
So the thing you've been

16:57.099 --> 17:00.060
threatening to do all day

17:00.102 --> 17:03.314
but had no intention of doing,

17:00.102 --> 17:03.314
you did but didn't mean to?

17:03.356 --> 17:04.691
Yeah.

17:04.732 --> 17:06.275
You can yell

17:04.732 --> 17:06.275
at us now.

17:06.317 --> 17:07.944
(sighs)

17:07.986 --> 17:09.487
No, I guess I deserve it.

17:09.529 --> 17:12.072
I shouldn't have ratted

17:09.529 --> 17:12.072
on you guys.

17:12.114 --> 17:15.242
Mom was just really

17:12.114 --> 17:15.242
pressuring me about coming home

17:15.284 --> 17:16.243
and, well, I folded.

17:16.285 --> 17:17.871
Coming home?

17:17.912 --> 17:19.956
Yeah, she said if I wanted

17:17.912 --> 17:19.956
to come home for the summer,

17:19.998 --> 17:21.165
I had to tell her

17:19.998 --> 17:21.165
about the bike.

17:22.709 --> 17:26.253
But that's just a lame excuse.

17:26.295 --> 17:28.589
I'm sorry.

17:32.134 --> 17:36.096
Actually,

17:32.134 --> 17:36.096
that was a pretty good excuse.

17:36.138 --> 17:39.893
Wow, you have made

17:36.138 --> 17:39.893
a great deal here, Hal.

17:39.934 --> 17:42.311
Now, you just, uh,

17:39.934 --> 17:42.311
sign right there

17:42.353 --> 17:43.980
and she's all yours.

17:44.022 --> 17:46.273
Yeah, you know, I-I've

17:44.022 --> 17:46.273
been thinking...

17:46.315 --> 17:49.109
I think maybe I got

17:46.315 --> 17:49.109
a little overexcited.

17:49.151 --> 17:50.778
Aw, that's just the jitters.

17:50.820 --> 17:53.280
They'll be long gone

17:50.820 --> 17:53.280
when you're roaring home

17:53.322 --> 17:54.949
in your brand-new

17:53.322 --> 17:54.949
Porsche.

17:54.991 --> 17:56.325
Just sign.

17:54.991 --> 17:56.325
No, I think

17:56.367 --> 17:57.994
maybe we should

17:56.367 --> 17:57.994
do this another time

17:58.036 --> 17:59.286
because I-I'm not

17:58.036 --> 17:59.286
feeling very well

17:59.328 --> 18:00.371
and my wife has the flu...

18:00.413 --> 18:01.915
I'll tell you what--

18:01.956 --> 18:04.124
let's throw in

18:01.956 --> 18:04.124
the new chrome turbo wheels

18:04.166 --> 18:06.586
and free car washes

18:04.166 --> 18:06.586
for a year-- just sign.

18:06.627 --> 18:09.129
I can't.

18:09.171 --> 18:12.926
But, Hal...

18:12.967 --> 18:15.762
you put your initials

18:12.967 --> 18:15.762
by this number.

18:15.803 --> 18:17.137
Sorry.

18:17.179 --> 18:19.766
Maybe some other time.

18:21.183 --> 18:23.143
Hal, will you do me

18:21.183 --> 18:23.143
one favor?

18:23.185 --> 18:25.312
One favor, now,

18:23.185 --> 18:25.312
I want you just to...

18:25.354 --> 18:28.148
stick your head in the car

18:25.354 --> 18:28.148
one last time, okay?

18:28.190 --> 18:30.150
I want you to smell

18:28.190 --> 18:30.150
the leather,

18:30.192 --> 18:32.152
take another look

18:30.192 --> 18:32.152
at that console,

18:32.194 --> 18:34.154
and tell me you don't

18:32.194 --> 18:34.154
want this car.

18:34.196 --> 18:35.155
Go ahead, do it.

18:35.197 --> 18:38.618
Come on.

18:38.659 --> 18:40.160
(inhaling)

18:40.202 --> 18:41.788
So what do you say?

18:41.829 --> 18:44.164
(retching)

18:44.206 --> 18:46.125
I told you I was sick!

18:55.217 --> 18:56.761
Oh, my God!

18:56.803 --> 18:57.845
You guys,

18:57.887 --> 18:59.346
we can save Francis.

18:59.388 --> 19:00.848
What?!

18:59.388 --> 19:00.848
Think about it--

19:00.890 --> 19:02.182
every time

19:00.890 --> 19:02.182
Mom gets mad,

19:02.224 --> 19:04.393
she forgets about

19:02.224 --> 19:04.393
everything else in the world

19:04.435 --> 19:06.186
except for the things

19:04.435 --> 19:06.186
she's mad at.

19:06.228 --> 19:07.814
That focus is the key

19:06.228 --> 19:07.814
to her power.

19:07.855 --> 19:08.815
So?

19:08.856 --> 19:10.190
So Mom won't care so much

19:10.232 --> 19:11.567
about sending Francis

19:10.232 --> 19:11.567
to a work farm

19:11.609 --> 19:13.987
if she's busy being mad

19:11.609 --> 19:13.987
at someone else, like at us.

19:14.028 --> 19:15.404
We can do that.

19:15.446 --> 19:17.197
Yeah.

19:15.446 --> 19:17.197
You don't

19:15.446 --> 19:17.197
understand.

19:17.239 --> 19:19.366
We're going to have to get

19:17.239 --> 19:19.366
in real trouble,

19:19.408 --> 19:22.202
more trouble than we've ever

19:19.408 --> 19:22.202
been in, in our entire lives.

19:22.244 --> 19:25.205
And we can't make it look

19:22.244 --> 19:25.205
like we're doing it on purpose.

19:25.247 --> 19:28.042
I just want you guys to

19:25.247 --> 19:28.042
know what you're in for.

19:28.084 --> 19:29.919
We owe it to him.

19:36.467 --> 19:38.052
Okay, we got

19:36.467 --> 19:38.052
Dad's skating trophy,

19:38.094 --> 19:39.804
Mom and Dad's

19:38.094 --> 19:39.804
wedding portrait,

19:39.846 --> 19:41.055
Mom's favorite lamp.

19:42.264 --> 19:45.434
No, Dewey, it's stuff

19:42.264 --> 19:45.434
they  like, not you.

19:45.476 --> 19:46.602
Oh.

19:46.644 --> 19:47.645
Good!

19:47.687 --> 19:49.605
Paint?!

19:49.647 --> 19:50.857
Yeah.

19:50.898 --> 19:53.026
That way, we not only

19:50.898 --> 19:53.026
destroy the stuff;

19:53.067 --> 19:54.234
we take out

19:53.067 --> 19:54.234
the driveway,

19:54.276 --> 19:56.236
splash on the house

19:54.276 --> 19:56.236
and, with any luck,

19:56.278 --> 19:57.822
get some

19:56.278 --> 19:57.822
collateral damage

19:57.864 --> 19:59.239
to the neighbors.

19:59.281 --> 20:00.407
What a waste!

20:00.449 --> 20:01.826
For any other reason

20:01.868 --> 20:04.620
this would've been

20:01.868 --> 20:04.620
the funnest thing ever.

20:04.662 --> 20:06.039
(watch beeps)

20:06.080 --> 20:07.247
Okay, guys...

20:07.289 --> 20:10.250
have the last candy bars

20:07.289 --> 20:10.250
of your childhood.

20:17.466 --> 20:20.094
(cheerfully goofy):

20:17.466 --> 20:20.094
Hey! Time to wake up!

20:20.136 --> 20:22.055
Hey!

20:20.136 --> 20:22.055
Time to wake up!

20:22.096 --> 20:26.893
Hey! Time to wake up!

